g.text: While the area is not recovered, the accumulated costs of not being able to use part of the benefits provided by the rivers should be accounted for, considering lost job opportunities in fishing, tourism, and worsening of the quality of drinking water.
ORIGINAL CONDITION AND (LOST) BENEFITS OF NATURE
This area must be restored for the ecosystem to return minimally to its previous conditions, a complex process that takes many years to generate results.
The extraction of 1 kg of gold of gold moves about around 15 thousand m3 of sediments, generating erosion, silting and sedimentation of rivers.
